text: Eqlid County () is a county in Fars Province in Iran. The capital of the county is Eqlid.Gitashenasi Province Atlas of Iran اطلس گیتاشناسی استان‌های ایران At the 2011 census, the county's population was 93,975, in 25,077 families.مرکز آمار ایران The county is subdivided into three districts: the Central District, Sedeh District, and Hasanabad District. The county has four cities: Eqlid, Sedeh, Dezhkord & Hasanabad. == References == == Other websites == Category:Counties in Fars Province
